## 3. `FoundItem` type has redundant `"builtin"` / `"command"` variants

**Severity:** Good-to-fix (types correctness)

```ts
type FoundItem =
  | { kind: "builtin"; item: SlashCommandInfo }
  | { kind: "command"; item: SlashCommandInfo }
  | { kind: "tool"; item: ImportedToolInfo };
```

Both `"builtin"` and `"command"` carry the same `SlashCommandInfo` payload. The `kind` discriminant is used only for display in `showCandidates` (line ~218). The source is already available via `cmd.source` (a `"SlashCommandSource"` string from the agent).

**Suggested fix:**
```ts
type FoundItem =
  | { kind: "command"; source: "extension" | "skill" | "prompt"; item: SlashCommandInfo }
  | { kind: "tool"; item: ImportedToolInfo };
```

Then update `wrapCommand()` (line 154) to include `source`. The `showCandidates` `kindLabel` line would switch on `match.kind` and use `match.source` for commands. This is 3 lines of cleanup but eliminates a phantom discriminated union.

**Bonus benefit:** This removes the only usage of the `"builtin"` kind, making the `"command"` kind sufficient.

