## 5. `types.ts` — manual mirrors risk silent divergence

**Severity:** Good-to-fix (upstream alignment risk)

### `Model` — local copy (types.ts line 12)
The actual `Model<TApi>` is defined in `@mariozechner/pi-ai/dist/types.d.ts:377` and has many more fields (`api`, `provider`, `baseUrl`, `reasoning`, `input`, `cost`). The extension only reads `id`, `name`, `provider`, so the local minimal interface is pragmatic.

**Issue:** `Model<TApi>` is NOT re-exported from `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`. Importing directly would require a sub-path import (`@mariozechner/pi-ai`), which is fragile since `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent` doesn't re-export it.

### `CoreThemeInfo` — local copy (types.ts line 20)
The actual `ThemeInfo` is at `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent/dist/modes/interactive/theme/theme.d.ts:32`:
```ts
export interface ThemeInfo { name: string; path: string | undefined; }
```

This matches the local copy exactly. The type is NOT re-exported from the agent's `dist/index.d.ts` entry point — it lives in a theme sub-path module.

**Recommendation:**
Add a `@see` JSDoc comment linking to the upstream type definition and note that these are minimal interfaces. Consider whether `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent` might re-export `ThemeInfo` in a future version (the `getAllThemes()` API in `ExtensionAPI` returns `ThemeInfo[]`-compatible shape, suggesting it's a public concept). A comment like:

```ts
/**
 * @see {@link https://github.com/mariozechner/pi-coding-agent/blob/main/src/modes/interactive/theme/theme.ts#L32
 *       ThemeInfo} in pi-coding-agent (not re-exported from main entry)
 */
export interface CoreThemeInfo { ... }
```

**Not a blocker** — both interfaces are stable and minimal by design.

